      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Ok, I've done some testing with tape-stretching\nThe 3 images, in order; are 3mm, 6mm, and 8mm stretch heights changed by changing out the material underneath. \nUnder any circumstance I think this is worth pursuing if only for the fact that it tightens the tape up like a drum which should help to keep the tape from tenting with the pusher from the bottom that comes and pushes the die off the tape. In addition to the clearance gained from the stretch.",
      "author": {
        "id": "756011607603019777",
        "name": "anfroholic",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Andrew Wingate",
        "color": null,
