    {
      "id": "1510177006602686605",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-30T07:04:16.106+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "All this brings us to ask whether I try to incorporate the stretcher into the holder in the machine, or if we want to get a separate machine that does the stretching. \nThere are stretch rings that you can buy and these are the smallest in the 10\" range and the 8\" ones are too small. _I am not sure why this is... but that's how it is_\nLooking at the ring inside the dicing frames we have been provided, we may be able to use the professional model, but it's still unclear whether it will work with the wafers mounted to the dicing frames. \nWe already have pneumatics on the current machine and all this is making me think that just having them stay on the frames the entire time would be a benefit and just have the stretch happen when we clamp the frame in. \n@Tim 'mithro' Ansell",
      "author": {
        "id": "756011607603019777",
        "name": "anfroholic",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Andrew Wingate",
